divs: sighting detailsi was standing by a fence photographing a 747-200 owned by evergreen international. after taking one photograph, and glancing at the image to check its quality, i heard some men at a nearby federal express loading dock shout "hey, look at that" i immediately photographed a disk shaped object moving from left to right. the camera caught the disk as it was above the 747, then again as it zipped up and into the sky. this vehicle made no sound of which i was aware, and there was no aircraft in the area as i also had an aviation band scanner with me. the disk to my eyes appeared to "shimmer" as it flew along, and appeared faceted on the top. i cannot even suggest the velocity of the disk when it left. i was holding the camera stead and the image is streaked. i am unsure how to calculate its velocity at this point. the object left my field of vision due to its velocity. there was no sonic boom, or other sound from this disk shaped "thing." image one shows the disk over the 747's tail. image two shows the disk, in the upper right portion of the photograph as it exited. these photographs were 3\4ths of a second apart.
